<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In the stack example it looks like the comment about the Your_View_Helper and My_View_Helper got switched:</p>

<p>$view = new Zend_View();
// Add /path/to/some/helpers with class prefix 'My_View_Helper'
$view-&gt;addHelperPath('/path/to/some/helpers', 'My_View_Helper');
// Add /other/path/to/helpers with class prefix 'Your_View_Helper'
$view-&gt;addHelperPath('/other/path/to/helpers', 'Your_View_Helper');</p>

<p>// now when you call $this-&gt;helperName(), Zend_View will look first for
<em>// "/path/to/some/helpers/HelperName" using class name</em>
// "Your_View_Helper_HelperName", then for
<em>// "/other/path/to/helpers/HelperName.php" using class name</em>
// "My_View_Helper_HelperName", and finally for
// "Zend/View/Helper/HelperName.php" using class name
// "Zend_View_Helper_HelperName".</p>

<p>Shouldn't the comments be :</p>

<p><em><em>// "/other/path/to/helpers/HelperName.php" using class name</em></em>
// "Your_View_Helper_HelperName", then for
<em><em>// "/path/to/some/helpers/HelperName" using class name</em></em>
// "My_View_Helper_HelperName", and finally for
// "Zend/View/Helper/HelperName.php" using class name
// "Zend_View_Helper_HelperName".</p>

